{
  "texts": [
    "Our investigation primarily focuses on skeletal data acquired through Kinect camera technology; however, our model demonstrates versatility by not relying exclusively on Kinect.",
    "An RGB camera can also be employed because our models are constructed utilizing joint coordinates.",
    "Nevertheless, additional processing is essential to extract skeletal joints.",
    "Two viable approaches for using RGB cameras as a primary sensor are OpenPose [62] Fig. 2 Overview of the Methodology and BlazePose [63].",
    "OpenPose and BlazePose are widely adopted solutions for extracting skeletal joints from the human body."
  ]
}